a little about me


I'm a full-stack web developer and a student University of Minnesota coding bootcamp student. Looking for full time work in information technology or web development. On this site you can find some of my web dev work, film photography, and sound art work.

-. --- .--

I reside in Minneapolis, MN and my ultimate goal is to work in Norway. I've studyied Norwegian since 2018 and I also have professional experience using Spanish. My academic background is in sociocultural anthropology, with a focus on the ethnography of sound. During undergrad I took my audio engineering knowledge from music to make sensory ethnography work, or documentaries of human culture focused on the senses. My final project was to record the soundscape of Hidden Falls Regional Park in St. Paul, MN, juxtaposing urban noise with nature sound to learn about how people conceive of nature through sound.

With Hamline University, I had the opportunity to take a 2017 short course in Siem Reap, Cambodia to learn about the blossoming tourist industry around the Angkor temple complex. Another one of my favorite experiences in this field was working with other archaeologists on burial recovery sites around Minnesota, where we recovered disturbed Native American grave sites under the leadership of descendent communities. Here is a news story about one such site I worked on.

Thank you for visiting and take care!
